rning, I went to buy breakfast, and found that granny liu was lying in the front of the door with a big yellow, and I saw that she was dead.\r\nThe so-called food is blessed, originally for own children.', '12', '0');
INSERT INTO `p_accept` VALUES ('efcaf78f-73be-4432-81f4-786e5da25de8', '9e6422cc-d562-4684-a561-342273d490c2', 'dam', 'f9355508-164c-45b6-96d8-7e2c82127834', '0', null, '0', '0');
INSERT INTO `p_accept` VALUES ('f6ae5d02-b58d-4f34-ba07-9a14655a382d', 'c049f955-54e0-4ff1-97dd-0a84300ebf8a', 'social', '3cb867b2-236c-4e14-aeb4-d8fcd0129b33', '1', 'Rockefeller: refuse to condemn, refuse to push\r\nReading (408) comments (2)\r\nRockefeller: refuse to condemn, refuse to push\r\nDear John,\r\nIf I say not to be outdone, always think oneself is the world\'s wealthiest man Mr Andrew Carnegie comes to visit me, and asked me a very serious problem, would you be surprised?In fact, that\'s what the great blacksmith did.\r\nTwo days ago, Mr. Carnegie came to our kikwete.Maybe I smiling attitude, and we have a relaxed conversation atmosphere, melting the Mr Carnegie iron self-esteem, let him put down the shelf ask me: \"John, I know, you have led a group of very efficient.However, I don\'t think their talents are unmatched, but I am puzzled that they seem unbreakable and can easily defeat your competitors.I want to know, what kind of magic have you done to make them have that spirit, is it the power of money?\"\r\nI told him that the power of money is certainly not to be underestimated, but the power of responsibility is enormous.Sometimes, action comes not from ideas, but from responsibility.Standard oil companies are responsible for the spirit and know, \"what is my responsibility?What can I do to make things better?\"But I never talk about responsibilities or obligations. I just create a responsible business through my leadership style.\r\nI think this topic should be finished here, but my answer clearly stirred up Mr Carnegie\'s curiosity, he seriously ask me: \"John, can you tell me how you did it?\"\r\nLooking at Mr. Carnegie\'s humble manner, I could not refuse, I must tell the truth.I told him that if we want to survive forever, our leadership means categorically refusing to condemn anyone or anything for any reason.Censure is like a swamp. Once you fall in, you lose your footing and the direction you are going, and you will get stuck in the mire of hate and frustration.There is only one result: loss of respect and support.Once it\'s in this field, you\'re like a king who gives up the crown to the other person and can\'t control everything.\r\nI know that censure is the number one enemy to destroy leadership, and I know that there are no general winners in this world, no matter who will be defeated and defeated.So, when the problem comes up, I don\'t feel resentful, I just think: how can things get better?What actions can we take to remedy or repair our mistakes?Actively choose to move toward higher productivity and satisfaction.\r\nOf course, I won\'t let myself go.When bad things happen to us, I stop and ask myself a question: \"what is my responsibility?\"Returning to the original point, with a completely honest assessment of their role, can avoid the empty snooping of what others have done, or ask other people to change what, and so on.In fact, only if I focus on myself, I can regain the crown that I accidentally gave away.\r\nBut analyzing \"what my duties are\" doesn\'t mean blaming yourself.Self-accusation is the most insidious way to blame a trap, such as \"that was a stupid mistake!\"Such self-censure will only bring me into a trap of resentment and resentment, which is the same as any other reproach.In fact, \"what is my duty\" analysis is a powerful force and self-affirmation steps, when I know that the real question is not what they should do, but what should I do, I will not self-pity, and will only make yourself more powerful.The more powerful you are, the less influence others will have, and that\'s not a bad thing.\r\nIf I could see every obstacle as an opportunity to learn more about myself, rather than about what others have done to me, I could find a way out of the wall of leadership crisis.\r\nOf course, I never see myself as a savior or a savior.I ask myself: what should I be responsible for?Ask yourself: in what ways are the subordinates responsible for me?A leader\'s job is not to be fully informed and fully responsible.If I see myself as a brave and righteous messenger, ready to save the world, it will only lead to a crisis of leadership.A big part of my responsibility is to let others take responsibility for their own responsibility.If an employee for the matter of their immediate interests don\'t care, I don\'t believe such employees to have a strong desire to get it done, that he should leave, to service for others.\r\nThe feeling of responsibility on the shoulders can make people feel more and more excited.Nothing like a personal sense of responsibility, can stimulate and strengthen the ability of doing things, subordinates and entrust their responsibility, and let him know I fully trust to him, is undoubtedly the biggest help to him.Therefore, I will not take responsibility for my subordinates and be able to burden themselves.\r\nI don\'t just rely on demonstration to create the atmosphere and atmosphere of the company. My subordinates know my basic principles: there is no censure in standard oil company, no excuses!This is my philosophy, everyone knows it.I will not punish them for their mistakes, but I will not tolerate irresponsibility.Our belief is to pursue it thoroughly.Our motto is that support, encouragement, and respect will be fully embraced and redoubled.It would be intolerable to have an excuse not to provide a solution.\r\nWe rarely make any mistakes, because my door is always open to my subordinates, they can offer high opinions, or pure whining, but in a responsible way.The result is that we trust each other, because we know that everything needs to be discussed in the sunshine.\r\nMr. Carnegie, an excellent old student who didn\'t let me waste time, said on my end of the subject: \"in the midst of all the grumbles, good employees turn into a rabble!\"He\'s really smart.\r\nJohn, almost all of us have the defensive mentality of the real responsibility of the promotion committee, so that the phenomenon of the responsibility is everywhere.But it is a disaster.The way to avoid defense is to start listening.\r\nThe biggest challenge for a leader is how to create an environment where people feel more comfortable and honest than they are.Offer to invite others to present their ideas, and encourage them to say what they think by saying something like \"say a little more\" or \"I really want to hear your opinion\".Contrary to what the average person believes, in a conversation, the listener is the person who has power, not the presenter.\r\nUnbelievable?Think about the tone, focus, and content of the presenter, in fact, depending on the way you listen.Think of the difference between a person who is hostile and physically aggressive with a face, and a person who speaks to you in a way that is very attentive to you.When you listen to others simply, you take your defense off.You\'ll get these benefits: you\'ll have a better understanding of the underlying issues behind aggressive or angry language.You can get more information that can change your assumptions about the whole event.You\'ll have more time to organize your thoughts.\r\nThe presenter will feel that you value their opinion.The most exciting thing is that when you listen intently, the original presenter will be more willing to listen to you.\r\nReal listening is not defensive.Even if you don\'t like the message, you should listen to it and not respond immediately.Listening attentively is not a skill; it\'s more like an attitude.The skier, in every second of the time he encounters an obstacle, has a hundred per cent attention, and is absolutely not distracted to think about what he is going to say to his partner.Similarly, as an active listener, you give 100 percent of your attention to another person, and you don\'t blurt out what comes to mind.In this way, you go beyond preconceived notions and open your mind to a more meaningful and effective dialogue.\r\nFor so long, we have shaped our lives and shaped ourselves.This process will continue, and we will ultimately be responsible for our choices.Just as \"purpose\" determines your direction, rejection of censure will build a path towards your goal.\r\nLove your father', '12', '67');
